install-usb-gui (0.0.6) unstable; urgency=low

  [ Kel Modderman ]
  * install_fromiso_in_USB:
    - fix option with argument handling in getopts usage
    - don't hide what grub is doing, the method of hiding its output was
      suspicious anyway
    - add fromhd=LABEL= to default menu.lst template to ensure we probe only
      for the usb boot medium
    - fix x-un-i typo in copyright header
    - add valid_label() to sanitize user input
    - append a pseudorandom integer to fallback label name to help avoid
      volume label conflict
    - append arguments to script after -- break point to menu.lst
    - move trap statement to just before the main() part of script
    - remove --help output for --label, --toram and --persist. All cheatcodes
      that are wanted should be listed after --
    - fail if no distro-defaults installed
    - use FLL_MEDIA_NAME instead of self made string, we anchor the wanted
      device by unique label now, no need to obscure the iso name
    - put kernel image and initrd-img in /boot

  [ Joaquim Boura ]
  * handle better when running under live
    - When booted fromiso use the own iso if no other was given
    - when booted into toram force input from iso
    - created a man page.

